message.content:
1. The serum IL-10 levels in group B were significantly higher than those in group C.
2. The serum E-selectin levels in group B were significantly higher than those in group C.
3. The serum TNF-α levels did not differ among groups.
4. The significance level for the difference in serum IL-10 levels between group B and C was P<0.001.
5. The significance level for the difference in serum E-selectin levels between group B and C was P<0.05.
6. The significance level for the difference in serum TNF-α levels among groups was P>0.05.

messages.content:
